Step 1 :

Creating a pod in the ext-access namespace and define 2 containers namely :
	1. business-app should use the image bmuschko/nodejs-business-app:1.0.0 and expose the container port 8080.
	2.  The ambassador container uses the image bmuschko/nodejs-ambassador:1.0.0 and exposes the container port 8081.
	
YAML :

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: rate-limiter
  namespace: ext-access
spec:
  containers:
  - name: business-app
    image: bmuschko/nodejs-business-app:1.0.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 8080

  - name: ambassador
    image: bmuschko/nodejs-ambassador:1.0.0
    ports:
    - containerPort: 8081

step 2 :

Check the http reuest that it can accept going inside the container :

C:\Users\thani\Kubernetes>kubectl exec -it rate-limiter -n ext-access -c business-app -- sh
